"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The groupby function returns a DataFrameGroupBy object, and the apply function is then used to apply a function to each group. However, the result of the apply function is a Series with a MultiIndex, which is then assigned to the original DataFrame. This will cause an alignment issue because the index of the original DataFrame does not match the index of the result Series. To fix this, we need to reset the index of the result Series before assigning it to the original DataFrame.\", \"patch\": \"9c9\\n< df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1)))\\n---\\n> df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).reset_index(level=0, drop=True)\\n\"}"